{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "11", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "05", "M": "53", "S": "40"}}, "news": [{"title": "UP-RERA enables online complaints against excess transfer charges by promoters", "para": "The Uttar Pradesh Real Estate Regulatory Authority has made online complaint filing operational for allottees facing demands for transfer charges beyond the prescribed limits. Complaints can be filed through Form-M on the UP-RERA portal under the e-court mechanism, following the implementation of the 10th amendment to its General Regulations, 2019.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/rera/up-rera-launches-online-complaints-for-excess-transfer-charges-on-property-transfers/131002956?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-65492/131002956.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "rera"}, {"title": "Maharashtra to introduce property cards with valuation for all plots under proposed Land Titling Act", "para": "Maharashtra is set to introduce a Land Titling Act making property cards mandatory for all land parcels, reflecting their value. This move aims to provide globally valid proof of ownership, simplify transactions, and reduce property disputes. The legislation is expected to be finalized by July and presented to the assembly during the monsoon session.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/maharashtras-land-titling-act-property-cards-for-all-with-official-valuation/131002799?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-123358/131002799.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "SRA scraps 181 of 228 government joint venture projects in Mumbai", "para": "Nearly two years after initiating joint ventures for slum redevelopment, 181 out of 228 projects have been scrapped due to lack of progress and feasibility issues. State-run agencies like BMC, Mhada, and MMRDA will now implement fewer projects, with the remaining returning to SRA for redevelopment under new schemes.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/mumbais-sra-cancels-majority-of-slum-redevelopment-joint-ventures/131002619?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-158652/131002619.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}